\cf0 3. Recursion 
\f2 \uc0\u55358 \u56990 
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Recursion is when something solves a problem by asking a smaller version of the same problem.\
Imagine opening a Russian nesting doll:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Open the big doll.\
\ls7\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Inside is a smaller doll.\
\ls7\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Open that one.\
\ls7\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Inside is an even smaller doll.\
\ls7\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Keep going until you reach the tiniest doll.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 That's recursion!\
