\cf0 Analysis\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 In this experiment, both the zero-shot and few-shot prompts produced the same classifications because the reviews contained clear sentiment indicators. However, few-shot prompting is most useful when dealing with ambiguous, domain-specific, or complex examples where the correct classification may not be obvious. By providing labeled examples, few-shot prompting helps the model better understand the desired output format and classification criteria, leading to more consistent and reliable results.\
